The Bundesbank intervened in the Tokyoforeign exchange market to buy a small amount of dollarsagainst marks through the Bank of Japan, dealers said.    The West German central bank bought dollars when the dollarwas at about 1.7770-80 marks. Dealers' estimates of theintervention amount varied from 100 mln to one billion dlrs.    Some dealers said the Bank of Japan appeared to haveundertaken small-lot mark-selling intervention on its ownaccount. REUTER&#3;